# 🚌 Istanbul Bus Tracker — Real-Time Transit API Application

A Python application that integrates with **Istanbul Metropolitan Municipality (IMM)**
open data APIs to provide real-time bus tracking, stop information, and fleet analytics.
Built for CSE 102 – Programming Practice, Spring 2024.

---

## 📌 Features

| Function | Description |
|---|---|
| `announcements(line_code)` | Fetches service announcements for a bus line |
| `stopping_buses()` | Lists door numbers of all currently stopped buses |
| `max_speeds()` | Returns the top 3 fastest buses in real time |
| `show_line_stops(line_code, direction)` | Lists all stops for a line and direction |
| `live_tracking(line_code, direction)` | Saves live bus + stop data and returns coordinates |

---

## 🚀 Usage

```python
# Get announcements for line 11H
print(announcements("11H"))
# Output: (2, ['TEPEÜSTÜ dan Saat 19:24 de hareket etmesi...', '...'])

# List all stops for line 19T, departure direction
print(show_line_stops("19T", "G"))
# Output: ['ATATÜRK BULVARI', 'SEYİD NİZAM CADDESİ', ...]

# Live tracking for line 122C
stops, buses = live_tracking("122C", "G")
# Also writes to where.js for map visualization
```

---

## 🗺️ Live Map Visualization

After running `live_tracking()`, open `where_is_my_bus.html` in a browser
to see real-time bus and stop positions on an interactive Istanbul map.

